bio.experienceSummary:
I've always had a passion for nurturing the growth of young minds, which led me to become a childcare provider. With over six years of experience caring for children of all ages, I have honed my skills in creating a safe, nurturing, and stimulating environment for kids to thrive.

My patient, calm, and friendly nature allows me to connect easily with children and build strong bonds. I believe in open communication with parents and provide regular updates about their child's day. Whether it's through written daily reports or regular phone calls, I ensure that parents are always informed and involved.

I'm comfortable enforcing household rules while prioritizing the child's well-being and following the parents' guidelines. My approach to playtime is varied, from engaging in outdoor sports and physical games to enjoying board games and puzzles, and incorporating educational games that promote learning.

I'm Myrriah-a passionate childcare provider and certified kids yoga instructor with over a decade of experience. I've spent 7 years as a nanny, including caring for multiple children at once (even two under 2) and managing nanny shares.

In addition to my childcare experience, I'm also a children's book author and former Preschool and Pre-K teacher with 6 years of teaching experience. I love incorporating developmentally appropriate activities, music and movement, and mindfulness into my care to keep kids learning and growing.

As a mom to a toddler, I know how important it is to find someone you can trust completely. I strive to be the nanny I would hire for my own child-nurturing, dependable, and full of creative energy.

If you're looking for someone who will treat your children with love, care, and enthusiasm, I'd love to connect with your family!

Please message me and I'll be sure to respond.

Thanks,
Myrriah

description.displayText: Myrriah is everything you want in a babysitter. Kind, engaged, communicative. She did a fabulous job watching my busy 15 month old boy and I can't wait to have her over again!
description.originalText: Myrriah is everything you want in a babysitter. Kind, engaged, communicative. She did a fabulous job watching my busy 15 month old boy and I can't wait to have her over again!

bio.experienceSummary:
As a caregiver, my passion lies in nurturing the growth and development of children. My three years of experience have equipped me with the skills to create a nurturing environment where children can thrive. I believe in fostering creativity and imagination while prioritizing safety and well-being.

My patient and friendly nature allows me to connect easily with children, while my calm demeanor helps diffuse any challenging situations. Open communication is essential, so I ensure regular updates to parents about their child's day, using their preferred method of communication.

I enjoy playing a variety of games with children, from outdoor sports and physical activities to board games and educational games that stimulate learning. My bilingualism in English and Spanish allows me to communicate effectively with a diverse group of families.

I am committed to providing reliable and flexible care, and I'm also happy to assist with travel-related tasks.

Hi there! My name is Claire and I recently graduated from Emory University with degrees in environmental science and political science. I have a wide variety of experiences working with children! I have been babysitting for four years, currently tutor students K-8 with Northside tutoring, and used to lead community gardens for elementary students. I play ultimate frisbee, love being outside, and am always excited to plan any sort of crafty activity! Please reach out if you have any questions :)

description.originalText: Claire was great with our kids!  She participated in multiple activities that our kids love (walk to the park, play board games, crafts).   She was on time and confirmed timing beforehand and easy to reach.  Would definitely recommend and will be reaching out to her for future care.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello my name is Rachel. I am 28 years old. I was born and raise in Atl, ga . I have been 2 wonderful kids 6&3 . I would describe my personality as outgoing, fun to be around, and approachable.


I started working with kids when I was 12 years old babysitting here and there I have work at 3 daycares . As of the current year I was an after school teacher. I have experience with ALL ages .


One thing you should know about me is I'm very easy going, and I love working with kids and very reliable communication is very important to me . My skills include communication and problem-solving and patience. 

If you have anymore questions please do not hesitate to ask .

description.originalText: So I want to say Rachel was GREAT with my kids. I was so nervous to have a stranger look after my kids and she made me feel really comfortable and treated my kids like they where hers . Her being a mom is a plus because she understands the importance of taking care of kids thank u Rachel

bio.experienceSummary:
Available for occasional help only. 

Hi I'm Kimberly! I'm a multifaceted individual with a diverse background that spans athletics, academia, and creative industries. I first made my mark as a former track and field athlete at the University of Georgia, where I majored in Advertising.

After my athletic and academic pursuits, I transitioned into the world of graphic and digital design.

During a hiatus from the graphic design world, I decided to purse my passion of working with kids and became an elementary school substitute teacher. I love engaging with kids and showing them creative ways of doing things. I love being busy and kids have way of always keep me on my toes. I have also been a nanny for many families and have thoroughly enjoyed my time with them.

Also, during my professional journey, I had the opportunity to work with The Home Edit, a renowned organization company. 

I can be described as a go-getter, free-spirited, and lively! :)

description.originalText: Kim is such a kind, professional, and fun babysitter. My little ones enjoyed spending the evening playing games, eating pizza, and relaxing with Ms. Kim. I am a 20 year veteran educator and I highly recommend Kim. She is definitely a 5 star babysitter. ✨✨✨

bio.experienceSummary: I am a career Nanny with 14years of experience working with children. My experiences include working as a nanny (live-in and out) as well as working in multiple childcare facilities. I have experience working with various ages from newborns to school age. I have worked with multiples twins as well as triplets. I'm willing to do light meal prep and clean as needed. I can transport children to and from various activities. I am currently seeking weekend babysitting positions.

description.displayText: Danielle was our nanny for several months. She was great at planning exciting days and excursions for our children and I always knew our children were safe with her. She was on time to each shift, completed the responsibilities laid out in our contract and worked to act on any feedback immediately. She was thoughtful and had our girls work on projects and presents to give to my husband and myself on Father's Day and my birthday which was sweet and touching. Sadly our nanny arrangement didn't work out as the "fit" just wasn't there with her and my children, but I would recommend her as a nanny. She was hard working, punctual, and took feedback well. Unfortunately sometimes the kids personalities just don't mesh and we just needed to find a better fit. However she is a great, dependable childcare provider and I wouldn't hesitate to recommend her to others.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi! My name is Abby, and I am young, working professional in the Brookhaven area. While my 9-5's are quite boring, I truly enjoy children and would love to have some light-hearted fun in the evenings.
I have a decade of experience working with kids of all ages, a background in education and owning my own tutoring business, and six years of being a caregiver to children with disabilities.

Hello! I have been babysitting for over 15 years and have worked with ages 2 months and up to 10 years. I am a neonatal intensive care unit nurse at Emory Decatur Hospital. I am CPR and First Aid Certified with a clean driving record. I focus on keeping the infants/children entertained without much screen time if that is ok with the parents and keep them on their schedule. I enjoy focusing on playing with toys and reading, taking walks with kids, going to the park, and enjoying time outside. I often bring crafts and activities with me to make it special when a babysitter comes. I am comfortable with all basic necessity tasks such feeding, bathing, diapering, and putting to bed. I am well versed on Moms on Call and Taking Care Babies routines. I am happy to meet with you and provide references!

description.displayText: Avery has worked with our family for about two years and she is the best sitter we've ever had. She is a natural with kids, always on time, and very trustworthy. Our daughter loves her, and so do we!

bio.experienceSummary: I'm an experienced childcare provider with a passion for nurturing children's growth and development. I've been caring for children of all ages for over 16 years and have a natural ability to connect with them, creating a safe and nurturing environment where they can thrive. I'm patient, calm, and responsible, and I love using my creativity and energy to engage children in fun and educational activities. I'm also very comfortable enforcing household rules and communicating with parents about their child's day or any issues that arise. I'm seeking a position where I can use my skills and experience to positively impact the lives of children and their families. I'm available to care for up to two children, and my availability is flexible. I have some college education and am certified in CPR and First Aid. I have a car, am comfortable with pets, and only speak English.

description.originalText: Caring, courteous and willing to go above and beyond! Truly offers a loving touch! Our family absolutely loves Ms.Angel! Hands down best nanny ever!
